'''Eva-Lena Lundgren''' (born 1961)<ref name="worcester">{{cite news |url=http://archive.worcesternews.co.uk/2006/6/7/414445.html |title=25 years ago June 5, 1981 |date=2006-06-07 |work=[[Worcester News|The Worcester Evening News]] |accessdate=2009-11-22 |quote=The 19-year-old [as of June 1981], who was in the Midlands for the Miss Europe finals, had hit international headlines, had hit international headlines}}{{Dead link|date=December 2016}}</ref> is a Swedish model,<ref name="gentid"/> and a former [[Miss Sweden]] 1981.<ref name="worcester"/><ref name="gentid">{{cite web |url=http://www.sverigesman.se/historik/fr_sverige/genom_tiderna.htm |title=Fröken Sverige Genom Tiderna |date=2007-06-25 |publisher=BossaNova Business AB |work=Sveriges Man |language=Swedish |quote=Jag är utbildad Montessoripedagog och mamma till tre barn. Jag är gift och bor i Amsterdam. |accessdate=2009-11-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100821132501/http://www.sverigesman.se/historik/fr_sverige/genom_tiderna.htm |archivedate=2010-08-21}}</ref><ref>[http://www.sverigesman.se/historik/fr_sverige/genom_tiderna.htm Fröken Sverige genom tiderna] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100821132501/http://www.sverigesman.se/historik/fr_sverige/genom_tiderna.htm |date=2010-08-21 }}, accessed 2010-05-19 {{sv icon}}</ref>
Later in 1981 she finished in third place at the [[Miss Universe 1981]] pageant and fourth place at [[Miss Europe]]. Lundgren was awarded the [[Miss Scandinavia]] crown the same year in [[Helsinki]], [[Finland]].{{citation needed|date=November 2009}}

She later became '''Eva-Lena Pilotti'''. {{as of|2007}}, she was a [[Montessori method|Montessori]] Latin and Greek teacher in [[Amsterdam]], [[Netherlands]], and had three children.<ref name="gentid"/>

