{{use American English|date=January 2016}} {{use mdy dates|date=January 2016}} {{infobox journal | title = The Journal of Blacks in Higher Education | cover = | discipline = Education | abbreviation = J. Blacks High. Educ. | editor = Robert Bruce Slater | publisher = BRUCON Publishing | country = United States | history = 1993-present | frequency = Quarterly | impact = | impact-year = | website = https://www.jbhe.com | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = | link2-name = | ISSN = 1077-3711 | eISSN = 2326-6023 | CODEN = | LCCN = 93664388 | OCLC = 40892795 | JSTOR = 10773711 }} '''''The Journal of Blacks in Higher Education''''' is a former [[academic journal]], now an online [[magazine]], for [[African American]]s working in [[academia]] in the United States.
==History== The journal was established as a quarterly in 1993 by [[Theodore Cross]], a "champion of civil rights"<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/03/04/business/04cross.html |title=Theodore Cross Dies at 86, a Champion of Civil Rights |last=Fox |first=Margalit |date=3 March 2010 |work=[[The New York Times]] |accessdate=10 November 2016}}</ref> and the journal's longtime [[editor-in-chief]].<ref>{{cite book |last=Wilson |first=Ida Elizabeth |editor=Beverly Lindsay |others=Manuel J. Justiz |title=The Quest for Equity in Higher Education: Toward New Paradigms in an Evolving Affirmative Action Era |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=pMNCl1LuejoC&pg=PA53 |year=2001 |publisher=[[SUNY Press]] |isbn=9780791450611 |pages=33–62 |chapter=Judicial and Legal Perspectives on Student Affirmative Action in Higher Education}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Thernstrom |first1=Stephan |last2=Thernstrom |first2=Abigail |title=America in Black and White: One Nation, Indivisible |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=N3esfeWwFWYC&pg=PA637 |year=2009 |publisher=[[Simon & Schuster]]|isbn=9781439129098 |page=637}}</ref> The last print issue appeared in 2010.<ref name=LC>{{cite web |url=http://lccn.loc.gov/93664388 |title=The Journal of Blacks in Higher Education |work=Library of Congress Catalog |publisher=[[Library of Congress]] |access-date= December 3, 2015}}</ref><ref name="jstorjournal">{{cite web |title=The Journal of Blacks in Higher Education |url=https://www.jstor.org/journal/jblachigheduc | publisher = [[JSTOR]] |access-date=December 3, 2015}}</ref> Issues published between 1993 and 2010 are available on [[JSTOR]].<ref name="jstorjournal"/> However, the magazine still publishes articles on its website.<ref name="websiteabout">{{cite web |title=About JBHE |url=https://www.jbhe.com/about |work=The Journal of Blacks in Higher Education |access-date=December 3, 2015}}</ref> It reports and comments on statistical information pertaining to black students and faculty in the United States.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.slate.com/articles/life/counter_narrative/2014/01/adjunct_crisis_in_higher_ed_an_all_too_familiar_story_for_black_faculty.html |title=Adjunct crisis in higher ed: An all too familiar story for black faculty |last=Cottom |first=Tressie McMillan |authorlink=Tressie McMillan Cottom|date=24 January 2014 |work=[[Slate (magazine)|Slate]] |accessdate=10 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.adjunctnation.com/2004/01/01/37-a-review-of-ithe-journal-of-blacks-in-higher-educationi-and-iblack-issues-in-higher-educationi/ |title=A Review of ''The Journal of Blacks in Higher Education'' and ''Black Issues in Higher Education'' |last=Drozdowski |first=Mark J. |date=1 January 2004 |publisher=AdjunctNation.com |accessdate=10 November 2016}}</ref> According to Rhonda Sharpe and William Darity ("Schools Successful at Producing Black Male Graduates"), it is "a key resource for publicly consumable statistical reports about the status of blacks in higher education".<ref>{{cite book |last1=Sharpe |first1=Rhonda Vonshay |last2=Darity |first2=William A. |editor=Henry Taylor Frierson |others=James H. Wyche |title=Black American Males in Higher Education: Research, Programs and Academe |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=44fCBDIPrZYC&pg=PA315 |year=2009 |publisher=[[Emerald Group Publishing]] |isbn=9781849506434 |pages=79–116 |chapter=Where are Brothers in the Academy? Schools Successful at Producing Black Male Graduates}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|first=Jack|last=Greenberg|year=2004|title=Brown V. Board Of Education: Witness To A Landmark Decision|publisher=Twelve Tables Press|page=298}}</ref>
Its publisher is headquartered in [[Bartonsville, Pennsylvania]].<ref name="websiteabout"/>
